statement.p:
Show that Möbius geometry (\extC,\M) and the projective geometry (\Proj(\C^2),PGL(2)) are equivalent via the map \mu\colon \Proj(\C^2) \to \extC given by
\mu([\alpha,\beta]) = \begin{cases} \alpha/\beta \amp \beta\neq 0\\ \infty \amp \beta=0. \end{cases}
Comment: Observe that \mu is an extension of \pi_1\colon U_1\to \C given by \pi_1([x_0,x_1])=\frac{x_0}{x_1} (defined in ).
